Rule Description:
Format of email: local_part@domain_part

Requirements on local_part:
1.	Email must hv local_part, not start with the @
2.	Characters permitted: 
•	All alphabet & digits (A_Z, a_z, 0_9)
•	Special characters !#$%&'*+_/=?^_`{|}~
•	Dot/full stop (.), but not as starting or ending character or appearing consecutively, e.g. .John, John. or John..Lim not allowed. John.Lim is allowed.

Requirements on domain_part: Made of one or more non_blank parts separated by dots. Permitted characters for each part: 
•	All alphabet & digits (A_Z, a_z, 0_9)
•	Hyphen (_) but not as starting or ending character

e.g. ambank_home (one part only – no separation dots), gmail.com, yahoo.com.my etc.

Note: @ allowed in email Addr only as the separator between local_part & domain_part, not allowed in either part
rule_logic_desc: Complex email local and domain format with Entity Type
